article.headline: Oregon State 68, Portland State 52
article.story:
PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Hollye Chapman had 18 points, including
eight during a key first-half run, to lead Oregon State to a 68-52
win over Portland State on Wednesday.

The Beavers (4-2) finished their four-game road trip with a 2-2
record and defeated the Vikings (1-4) for the 23rd time in 29
meetings.

Jessica Jones added 11 points for the Beavers and Brina Chaney
had 10.

The Beavers led 15-13 after 12 minutes, but finished the half
with an 18-2 run and never looked back. Chapman started the run
with a 3-pointer and Leilani Estavan ended it with one.

The Vikings couldn't get closer than 12 points in the second
half and Jones' jumper with four minutes left gave the Beavers
their biggest lead of the night, 64-44.

Oregon State's shooting and passing was the difference. The
Beavers had a 22-5 advantage in assists and shot 51 percent from
the field and 57 percent from 3-point range.

The Vikings shot 29 percent and made one 3-pointer. Their bright
spot was a 21-for-23 performance at the line.

Sarah Hedgepeth led Portland State with 17 points and Heidi
Stuart added 12.
